   "source": [
    "# 🦀 Day 5: Middleware, Extractors, Shared State in Axum\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What is Middleware?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Middleware** is a layer in the request/response pipeline. Each request passes through middleware before reaching your handler, and the response passes back through. Use it for:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Logging / tracing\n",
    "- CORS headers\n",
    "- Authentication\n",
    "- Request timing\n",
    "- Rate limiting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    ":dep axum = \"0.7\"\n",
    ":dep tokio = { version = \"1\", features = [\"full\"] }\n",
    ":dep serde = { version = \"1\", features = [\"derive\"] }\n",
    ":dep serde_json = \"1\"\n",
    ":dep tower-http = { version = \"0.5\", features = [\"cors\", \"trace\"] }\n",
    "\n",
    "// Dependencies loaded."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## tower-http for Common Middleware\n",
    "\n",
    "`tower-http` provides pre-built middleware (CORS, logging/tracing, compression, etc.). Axum uses Tower's `Service` trait, so middleware layers compose easily."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, routing::get};\n",
    "use tower_http::cors::{CorsLayer, Any};\n",
    "use tower_http::trace::TraceLayer;\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn hello() -> &'static str {
    "    \"Hello!\"
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// CORS: allow any origin (for development)\n",
    "let cors = CorsLayer::new()\n",
    "    .allow_origin(Any)\n",
    "    .allow_methods(Any)\n",
    "    .allow_headers(Any);\n",
    "\n",
    "// Trace: request logging (uses tracing crate)\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/\", get(hello))\n",
    "    .layer(cors)\n",
    "    .layer(TraceLayer::new_for_http());\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Router with CORS and Trace middleware layers.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Custom Middleware with `from_fn`\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `axum::middleware::from_fn` to create custom middleware. A middleware function receives the request and a `next` closure — call `next.run(request).await` to pass through."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, middleware, routing::get, body::Body, http::Request};\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn logging_middleware(\n",
    "    request: Request<Body>,\n",
    "    next: axum::middleware::Next,\n",
    ") -> axum::response::Response {\n",
    "    let method = request.method().clone();\n",
    "    let uri = request.uri().clone();\n",
    "    let response = next.run(request).await;\n",
    "    println!(\"{} {} -> {}\", method, uri, response.status());\n",
    "    response\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn index() -> &'static str { \"Index\" }\n",
    "\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/\", get(index))\n",
    "    .layer(middleware::from_fn(logging_middleware));\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Custom logging middleware wraps all routes.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Request Timing Middleware\n",
    "\n",
    "Measure how long each request takes: record start time before `next.run`, compute elapsed time after."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, middleware, routing::get, body::Body, http::Request};\n",
    "use std::time::Instant;\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn timing_middleware(\n",
    "    request: Request<Body>,\n",
    "    next: axum::middleware::Next,\n",
    ") -> axum::response::Response {\n",
    "    let start = Instant::now();\n",
    "    let response = next.run(request).await;\n",
    "    let elapsed = start.elapsed();\n",
    "    println!(\"Request took {:?}\", elapsed);\n",
    "    response\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn slow_handler() -> &'static str {\n",
    "    tokio::time::sleep(tokio::time::Duration::from_millis(10)).await;\n",
    "    \"Done\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/slow\", get(slow_handler))\n",
    "    .layer(middleware::from_fn(timing_middleware));\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Timing middleware measures request duration.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Shared Application State with `State`\n",
    "\n",
    "Use `axum::extract::State` to inject shared state into handlers. The state is cloned per request (via `Arc`), so it's cheap. Your state type must implement `Clone`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, extract::State, routing::get};\n",
    "use std::sync::Arc;\n",
    "\n",
    "#[derive(Clone)]\n",
    "struct AppState {\n",
    "    app_name: String,\n",
    "    version: u32,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn config_handler(State(state): State<AppState>) -> String {\n",
    "    format!(\"{} v{}\", state.app_name, state.version)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "let state = AppState {\n",
    "    app_name: \"MyApi\".to_string(),\n",
    "    version: 1,\n",
    "};\n",
    "\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/config\", get(config_handler))\n",
    "    .with_state(state);\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"State extractor injects shared AppState into handlers.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Arc&lt;AppState&gt; for Shared Mutable State\n",
    "\n",
    "For mutable state (e.g. in-memory storage), wrap it in `Arc<RwLock<T>>` or `Arc<Mutex<T>>`. The `Arc` makes it cheap to clone for `State`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, extract::State, routing::get, Json};\n",
    "use std::sync::{Arc, RwLock};\n",
    "use std::collections::HashMap;\n",
    "\n",
    "#[derive(Clone, Default)]\n",
    "struct AppState {\n",
    "    counter: Arc<RwLock<u64>>,\n",
    "    cache: Arc<RwLock<HashMap<String, String>>>,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn get_counter(State(state): State<AppState>) -> String {\n",
    "    let count = *state.counter.read().unwrap();\n",
    "    format!(\"Counter: {}\", count)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "let state = AppState::default();\n",
    "\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/counter\", get(get_counter))\n",
    "    .with_state(state);\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"Arc<RwLock<T>> for shared mutable state across handlers.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Extension vs State Extractors\n",
    "\n",
    "| Extractor | Purpose |\n",
    "|-----------|----------|\n",
    "| `State<T>` | Injected via `Router::with_state`. Type must match exactly. |\n",
    "| `Extension<T>` | Injected via `Extension(thing)`. Can add per-request or per-route. |\n",
    "\n",
    "`State` is the primary way to share app-wide state. `Extension` is useful for adding things like a database connection per request."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use axum::{Router, extract::{State, Extension}, routing::get};\n",
    "\n",
    "#[derive(Clone)]\n",
    "struct AppState { name: String }\n",
    "\n",
    "struct DbConnection;\n",
    "\n",
    "async fn handler(\n",
    "    State(state): State<AppState>,\n",
    "    Extension(_db): Extension<DbConnection>,\n",
    ") -> String {\n",
    "    format!(\"App: {}\", state.name)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "let app = Router::new()\n",
    "    .route(\"/\", get(handler))\n",
    "    .with_state(AppState { name: \"MyApp\".into() })\n",
    "    .layer(axum::Extension(DbConnection));\n",
    "\n",
    "println!(\"State for app config, Extension for per-layer injection.\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🏋️ Exercise: Request Counter Middleware\n",
    "\n",
    "Add a middleware that increments a request counter stored in shared state. Expose a `GET /count` endpoint that returns the current count. Use `Arc<AtomicUsize>` for the counter so you can mutate it from the middleware."
   ]
  },
  {
